{
  "id": "019cf625-7dd3-7a72-90bd-355eec68ccab",
  "content": "siders</span><br><br>\n    <span class=\"prompt\">#</span> <span class=\"output\">Set system to on-demand GPU switching</span><br>\n    <span class=\"prompt\">$</span> <span class=\"cmd\">sudo <span class=\"highlight-val\">prime-select on-demand</span></span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"card\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-blue); margin-top: 8px;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-secondary);\">\n      <strong style=\"color: var(--text-primary);\">Fair note:</strong> Windows can also set per-app GPU via\n      <em>Settings &gt; Display &gt; Graphics</em> or NVIDIA Control Panel.\n      I haven't tried it myself &mdash; but it's a hint, not enforcement,\n      and apps can override it. Linux's <code style=\"color: var(--accent-amber);\">DRI_PRIME</code> works at the driver\n      level, making it harder to ignore.\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">05 / 08</div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<!-- SLIDE 6: THE PORT WIRING DISCOVERY              -->\n<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">The Real Aha Moment</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\">\n    Your Monitor Cable<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-purple\">Chooses Your GPU</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 20px;\">\n    I discovered my laptop's ports are wired to <em>different</em> GPUs.\n  </div>",
